AGI - China is refusing the conference for the <a href="https://www.agi.it/estero/news/2024-05-30/ucraine-biden-autorizza-uso-armi-colpire-russia-26588420/">pace in Ukraine</a> next programme in Switzerland: is the charge formulated during a trip to Singapore> by President Volodymyr Zelensky.> "Unfortunately, today China is working to prevent countries from participating in the peace summit," said Zelensky to journalists at the edge of the security forum. Russia, again accused Zelensky, this time in a message on his Telegram profile, hit Ukraine with a thousand attacks in the only last week.
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
"Russia is trying to spread the total contempt for human life and constant terror," he wrote. The attacks, the leader of Kiev explained, have happened "with various types of missiles, anti-aircraft missiles and attack drones".&nbsp; "To protect life in Ukraine with a sufficient number of air defense systems, to provide our soldiers with the necessary weapons with the necessary scope, to exert pressure on the terrorist state so that Russia does not have time to adapt: this is the way to approach peace," added Zelensky.
&nbsp;
< blockquote
"Russian terror must lose. The world is able to provide for this"
</blockquote
&nbsp;
China has made it clear that President Xi Jinping will not participate in the summit for peace while neither the White House leader has now dissolved the reserve. "We are disappointed that some world leaders have not yet confirmed their participation in the peace summit," said Zelensky in Singapore without mentioning the <a href="https://www.agi.it/tag/cina/">Cina</a> or the United States. More than a hundred countries and organizations have committed to participating in the summit scheduled for mid-June in Switzerland, > said the leader of Kiev, urging the countries of the Asia-Pacific region to do so. In recent days, China had said that it considers "difficult" to participate in this summit if Russia is not invited, a statement approved by Moscow.&nbsp; "Otherwise, the conference will hardly play a substantial role in the return of peace," explained a spokesman for the Beijing Foreign Ministry. In Singapore, Zelensky met with U.S. Defense Minister Lloyd Austin, > a meeting that defined "very positive". Pentagon spokesman, General Pat Ryder, said in a briefing that Austin reiterated "the constant support of the United States to Ukraine in the face of Russian aggression".&nbsp;
